{{infobox country at games | NOC = BAR | NOCname = [[Barbados Olympic Association]] | games = Olympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.olympic.org.bb }} | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 1 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Barbados|competition=Summer Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = {{flagIOC|BWI|1960 Summer}} (1960) }} '''[[Barbados]]''' first competed at the '''[[Summer Olympic Games]]''' in [[1968 Summer Olympics|1968]], and has participated in each Games since then, missing only the [[1980 Summer Olympics]] by participating in the [[American-led boycott of the 1980 Summer Olympics|American-led boycott]] of those games. The country's only Olympic medal to date is a bronze won by sprinter [[Obadele Thompson]] in the men's 100 metres at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]].
Barbados competed as part of the [[West Indies Federation]] in [[British West Indies at the 1960 Summer Olympics|1960]]. Barbadian athlete [[James Wedderburn (athlete)|James Wedderburn]] was part of the 4 × 400 m relay team which won the bronze medal that year.
Barbados has never competed in the [[Winter Olympic Games]] ([[List of participating nations at the Winter Olympic Games|list]]).
