{{Infobox venue | name = Álvaro Sánchez Silva Coliseum | image = | image_caption = | nickname = | address = | location = [[Neiva]], [[Huila Department|Huila]] | coordinates = | type = Indoor Sporting Arena | genre = | built = | opened = | renovated = 2010<ref name="te">[http://www.lanacion.com.co/2010/07/12/instalan-maderamen-en-el-coliseo-de-neiva/ Instalan maderamen en el coliseo de Neiva] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927110505/http://www.lanacion.com.co/2010/07/12/instalan-maderamen-en-el-coliseo-de-neiva/ |date=2011-09-27 }}, Diario La Nación.</ref> | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | construction_cost= | former_names = | seating_type = | seating_capacity = 8000 | website = }}
The '''Coliseo Álvaro Sánchez Silva''', is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Neiva]], [[Huila Department|Huila]], [[Colombia]]. It is the most important sporting facility in Huila after the [[Estadio Guillermo Plazas Alcid]]. It has been recognized as having one of the best basketball courts in Colombia.<ref name="mejores">[http://elperiodicodeportivo.com.co/index.php?modulo=articulos&accion=verArticulo&id=1311 “El coliseo, es uno de los mejores del país”: Edgar Moreno], El Periódico Deportivo.</ref> It is used mainly for [[basketball]] events. The capacity of the arena is 8000 people.
It has hosted several national and international events such as the [[South American Basketball Championship 2010]]. It is also the venue for the "Elección y Coronacion Reina Nacional del Bambuco" during the [[Festival Folclórico y Reinado Nacional del Bambuco]].
