'''Dilhara Salgado''' (born 25 March 1983) is a Sri Lankan archer. She attended Methodist College, Colombo and is a member of the Sri Lanka Air Force Archery Club.<ref name="Akbar">{{cite news|last1=Akbar|first1=Rangi|title=Dilhara aims arrows at 2012 London Olympics|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/110814/Sports/spt05.html|accessdate=31 October 2017|work=Sunday Times Sri Lanka|date=14 August 2011}}</ref> She competed in the [[2011 World Archery Championships]] in Turin, Italy, scoring 1289.<ref name="Akbar"/>

Salgado has also participated in the [[2006 Asian Games]] and in the [[2010 Asian Games]]. She competed at the Olympic qualification tournament in the United States in an attempt to reach the [[2012 Summer Olympics]].<ref name="island">{{cite news|title=Archer optimistic of Olympics berth|url=http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=54505|accessdate=31 October 2017|work=The Island|date=15 June 2012}}</ref>

In the [[2016 South Asian Games]], she was part of the Sri Lankan women's archery team which won the silver medal in the [[Archery at the 2016 South Asian Games|Archery event]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Sports/2016-02-09/India-continues-dominance-with-76-Gold/206004|title=India continues dominance with 76 Gold|website=The Hans India|language=en|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archives.dailynews.lk/2006/08/19/spo33.asp|title={{!}}{{!}} Sport|website=archives.dailynews.lk|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref>

