{{Infobox football club | clubname = Hazyna | image =HazynaAshgabatFC.jpg | fullname = Hazyna sport kluby | nickname = ''Students'' | founded = 2015 |dissolved= 2016 | ground = [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]] | capacity = | stadium = Stadium of [[Turkmen State Institute of Economics and Management|TSIEM]] | owner = | chairman = | mgrtitle = | manager = | league = [[Turkmenistan League|Ýokary Liga]] | season = [[2015 Ýokary Liga|2015]] |position = 7 }} '''Hazyna Sport Club''' ({{lang-tk|Hazyna sport kluby}}) was a [[Turkmenistan]] professional [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Ashgabat]], formerly of the [[Ýokary Liga]]. It is the football team of the [[Turkmen State Institute of Economics and Management]].
== History == The team was established in February 2015. Taking into account the growing popularity of football among students [[Football Federation of Turkmenistan]] made an exception by allowing the team to participate in the [[Ýokary Liga]] without a selection in the Turkmenistan First League.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://turkmenistan.gov.tm/?id=8304|title=Туркменистан: золотой век|publisher=turkmenistan.gov.tm|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://turkmenportal.com/blog/4535|title=Футбольные болельщики, запаситесь терпением: до старта чемпионской гонки осталось шесть дней-Спорт-Turkmenportal.com|publisher=turkmenportal.com|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref> The new club was headed by [[Ahmet Agamyradow]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://turkmenportal.com/blog/4623|title="Алтын асыр" и "Шагадам" на классе побеждают соперников, а "Мерв" вырывает победу на последних минутах-Спорт-Turkmenportal.com|first=|last=ihyzmatlary.com|publisher=turkmenportal.com|accessdate=20 July 2016}}</ref> At 2016 Hazyna SK folded, ceasing to exist as a professional football club.
