'''Ken Johnson''', better known as "'''Pinto Ron'''", (born 1958<ref name="'Pinto Kenny': Extreme fan goes the distance for Bills">{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=BN&p_theme=bn&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=1140CB95A1799C50&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|title='Pinto Kenny': Extreme fan goes the distance for Bills|last=Gaughan|first=Mark|date=September 7, 2006|publisher=The Buffalo News Archives|accessdate=12 October 2010}}</ref>) is a [[Buffalo Bills]] fan known for attending every single Bills home and away game and hosting a tailgate party since 1994.<ref name="The One and Only Pinto Guy" /><ref name="RESULT TAKES WIND OUT OF BUFFALO FANS">{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/446637851.html?dids=446637851:446637851&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jun+21%2C+1999&author=CAROL+PHILLIPS%2C+THE+SPECTATOR&pub=The+Spectator&desc=RESULT+TAKES+WIND+OUT+OF+BUFFALO+FANS&pqatl=google|title=RESULT TAKES WIND OUT OF BUFFALO FANS|last=Phillips|first=Carol|publisher=thestar.com|accessdate=12 October 2010}}</ref> He is known for his red [[Ford Pinto]] and antics cooking food on his car hood in a variety of objects such as a shovel and army helmet; furthermore, he holds a tradition of being doused in ketchup and mustard.<ref name="The One and Only Pinto Guy">{{cite web|url=http://www.billszone.com/mtlog/archives/2004/07/29/the_one_and_only_pinto_guy.php |title=The One and Only Pinto Guy |last=Brady |first=Philip 'The Philster' |publisher=BillsZone.com |accessdate=12 October 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721203114/http://www.billszone.com/mtlog/archives/2004/07/29/the_one_and_only_pinto_guy.php |archivedate=21 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> Most notably he served shots out of a bowling ball until he was forced to shut down by the [[National Football League]] (NFL)<ref name="Bowled over, Part I">{{cite news|url=http://www.buffalonews.com/city/article215362.ece|title=Bowled over, Part I|date=October 9, 2010|publisher=BuffaloNews.com|accessdate=12 October 2010}}</ref> Johnson moved his tailgate party to private property next to the stadium where the NFL has no jurisdiction and was able to resume serving bowling ball shots. He has been featured in multiple NFL Films,he also remains close and best friends with Scott Barry and<ref name="Ken Johnson back at Bills game">{{cite news|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=5644483|title=Ken Johnson back at Bills game|date=October 3, 2010|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=12 October 2010}}</ref> as well as the made-for-TV movie ''[[Second String (film)|Second String]]''.<ref name="The One and Only Pinto Guy" />

