The '''''Premio internazionale Giacinto Facchetti''''' ("''Il bello del calcio''") is a recognition established in 2006 awarded annually to a football personality for their honesty, correct behaviour, fair-play, and sportsmanship by the [[Milan]]-based Italian sports newspaper ''[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]''.
==History== The prize was conceived in 2006 by the newspaper's former director [[Candido Cannavò]] and the newspaper's director at the time [[Carlo Verdelli]], in honour of the late [[Italy national football team|Italy]] and [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]] defender [[Giacinto Facchetti]], following his death earlier that year on 4 September.<ref name="Giacinto Facchetti">{{cite web|url=http://www.lastoriasiamonoi.rai.it/biografie/giacinto-facchetti/51/default.aspx|title=Giacinto Facchetti|language=Italian|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref name="theguardian.com">{{cite web|title=Giacinto Facchetti|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2006/sep/11/guardianobituaries.football|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref> The distinction is awarded annually to a football personality who, like Facchetti, has stood out for their honesty, correct behaviour, fair-play, and sportsmanship.<ref name="Il bello del calcio">{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/10-11-2012/a-zanetti-premio-facchetti-bello-calcio-capitano-913172226064.shtml|title=Zanetti nel nome di Facchetti Il bello del calcio è il Capitano|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Azzurra Saggini|date=10 November 2012|accessdate=8 June 2016}}</ref>
