'''Savannah Dragway''' was an eighth-mile {{nowrap|(200 m)}} [[dragstrip]] used by the [[NHRA]] located near in [[Savannah, Georgia]]. The track opened as a quarter-mile {{nowrap|(400 m)}} facility in 1968, but safety concerns and rising insurance costs caused it to convert to the smaller distance in the mid-1980s. They were forced to close down at the end of 2005, this was because a neighbour filed many noise complaints and also because their lease expired.

An eighth-mile track called "Savannah River Dragway" opened in 2006 in [[Screven County]]. It is further from Savannah, {{convert|50|mi|km}} northwest of the old Savannah Dragway location.

